
The atom is the building block of all matter.
It is the smallest particle of an element that has the properties of that element.
It consists of a dense central nucleus surrounded by a cloud of negatively charged electrons.
The nucleus is made up of positively charged protons and electrically neutral neutrons.
An atom is made up of a nucleus and electrons.
The number of protons in the nucleus determines the identity of the atom.
The number of electrons determines the chemical behavior of the atom.
